Introduction

Bae Woo-hee is a South Korean singer and actress under Fly Up Entertainment. She made her official debut on May 24, 2012, upon joining the girl group Dal Shabet. Following the group's hiatus in 2017, Woohee participated in the survival show "The Unit" where she successfully qualified to be a member of the project girl group UNI.T.

In 2019, Wohee left Happy Face Entertainment and signed with Fly Up Entertainment. Since then, she has focused on acting, appearing in dramas such as "Business Proposal" and "Birthcare Center."
